  "prompt": "What are the pros and cons of Cal Poly, Pomona, in terms of academics, surrounding area, social scene, and campus look/feel?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of Cal Poly Pomona's pros and cons:\n\nAcademics:\nPros:\n- Strong engineering and agriculture programs\n- Learn-by-doing philosophy with hands-on education\n- Polytechnic focus on practical skills\n- Affordable in-state tuition\n- Good job placement rates\n\nCons:\n- Large class sizes in some programs\n- Some departments less prestigious than others\n- Limited research opportunities compared to research universities\n\nSurrounding Area:\nPros:\n- Close to Los Angeles\n- Near multiple freeways\n- Proximity to entertainment and job markets\n- Good weather year-round\n\nCons:\n- High cost of living in surrounding area\n- Traffic congestion\n- Limited public transportation\n- Suburban/semi-industrial location\n\nSocial Scene:\nPros:\n- Diverse student population\n- Active student clubs\n- Commuter-friendly campus\n- Some on-campus events and activities\n\nCons:\n- Primarily commuter school\n- Less vibrant campus social life\n- Limited on-campus housing\n- Fewer traditional college social experiences\n\nCampus Look/Feel:\nPros:\n- Large, spacious campus\n- Beautiful agricultural/landscape areas\n- Modern facilities\n- Agricultural and architectural variety\n\nCons:\n- Spread out campus\n- Some older buildings\n- Less scenic compared to some other California campuses",
